  "prompt": "How to reset Honeywell thermostat and erase schedule?",
  "response": "To reset a Honeywell thermostat and erase its schedule, the process varies slightly depending on the specific model. Here are general steps for different types:\n\n1. For most programmable thermostats:\n- Press the RESET or MENU button\n- Select \"Reset to Factory Default\" or \"Restore Factory Settings\"\n- Confirm the reset\n\n2. For touchscreen models (like RTH9580WF):\n- Go to MENU/SCHEDULE\n- Select RESET\n- Choose \"Reset All Settings\"\n- Confirm the reset\n\n3. For basic programmable models:\n- Press and hold RESET button (often located behind a small cover)\n- Hold for 5-10 seconds\n- Release when display changes\n\n4. For specific models like T9 or T6 Pro:\n- Go to MENU\n- Select SYSTEM\n- Choose RESET\n- Select \"Factory Reset\"\n- Confirm reset\n\n5. For manual reset:\n- Remove thermostat from wall plate\n- Remove batteries\n- Wait 5 minutes\n- Reinsert batteries\n\nPro Tips:\n- Consult your specific model's manual for exact instructions\n- Note model number for precise guidance\n- After reset, you'll need to reprogram settings and schedule",
